      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>I understand that's the \"correct\" response, but it feels so hollow. Talking to a professional or a friend just feels like more work, more performative energy I don't have. It's like everyone is telling me to keep running a marathon when my legs are already broken. I'm not even looking for \"solutions\" or \"transitions\" anymore. I just want the noise to stop. I want to finally just... be still. Does that even make sense? That I just want everything to be quiet?",
